    <TIER LANG_REF="en" LINGUISTIC_TYPE_REF="phrase-item"
        PARENT_REF="A_phrase-txt-xmf" TIER_ID="A_phrase-gls-en">
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4_flexid_e102df48-df25-4510-ad17-f62fe11e4dd6">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>There is a legend about this territory of Jvari and Tobavarchkhili Lake; I was assigned to record the legend when I was at school, in the eghth grade.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann393" ANNOTATION_REF="ann391_flexid_ad62b07b-6359-430c-a857-c20eebd1ff63">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>My neighbor, a great man who knew "The Knight in the Panther's Skin" by heart and he composed verses himself, such a man, it was Gali Samushia, and he told me it; and the legend was the following.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann826" ANNOTATION_REF="ann824_flexid_6a1423e8-e9e6-428d-8895-3815fa59bcc8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Ochokochi [goat-man] used to visit Jvari from Karachi. Karachi is situated in the North Caucasus, which is the Republic of Karachay-Cherkessia presently. He said that it as a giant man who came here, got hold of a girl he liked and took her away.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1369" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1367_flexid_7c94aca2-c13c-4d70-8470-899d00ffbfa0">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>He said that people of Jvari could do nothing to help, could not take over him, and they thus suffered.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1684" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1682_flexid_5053dfbd-a485-4b5e-985e-292c65b0429b">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>And, it was then when another giant man appeared, a kindheart man, and the man, Aramkhutu by name, [appeared, Aramkhutu by name.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1993" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1991_flexid_15b84b4f-0bd4-4227-a244-bfd94ddd88d2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>He was not a local resident but he appeared.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2140" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2138_flexid_668e31d3-fe0b-4555-a61a-f55ce3c3716a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>People of Jvari asked him for help.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2281" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2279_flexid_afc20f71-3c17-4b97-80a2-78417401ab08">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>They told him everyhting what happened, and he said "all right', and, that year, he met the man when he came there.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2526" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2524_flexid_f42dc4cd-e3db-4994-8cb5-1eb2ae553363">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>He walked here there is the mountain named Okhachkue, and there its name is Kvira (the mountain and there).</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2686" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2684_flexid_0b49db13-b29e-420d-b1d0-c3fe6b69ae3f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Running downhill here, there was the river Magana, and, on this side, there is Kvira, two thousand meters high, and, that side, there is Okhachkue. They both stand as brothers, and they are beautiful when look down at them from above.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3079" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3077_flexid_43092591-3ab0-45c6-b0f9-fcf950668275">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Well, in the mountains, there are wells, lowered spots in a triangular way.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3264" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3262_flexid_59207f39-3271-492a-8e45-0bb9e6b80883">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>In some places, snow remains, there is 'jishti' [snow trapped in the hunnel], and herdsmen keep things there, meat and various things.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3528" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3526_flexid_68df40d4-2a35-4685-b066-7a4da8b77db8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>There are a lot of spots like that both over this mountain and over that mountain.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3668" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3666_flexid_30fedf67-a5f0-4e89-b138-59471355d987">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Over the mountain of Kvira, there is Kvakantsalia. I'll tell you about it at the end of the legend. It is related to this.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3918" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3916_flexid_d8e3c5f6-5b27-445e-803c-e9af707a520f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>He arrived. When he looked directly hither, when he was over the mountain, Aramkhutu called him not to come down there because it was him who was there and not do it.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4282" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4280_flexid_4d210514-d74e-45da-8a14-f1761ad0467a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>And he asked who he was. The other one told him, and, in a word, then they decided to fight.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4473" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4471_flexid_4a91d3b6-a8cd-41f2-8842-b19747618bfe">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Aramkhutu stood on over Kvira and Ochokochi stood on over Okhachkue, and they began throwing rocks at each other.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4702" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4700_flexid_f27e6c83-2ac3-4dcb-9bd8-8f2a56b5dd7a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Well, the rocks they were throwing would be huge, right?!</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4902" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4900_flexid_df52ef5f-e0c1-4629-ba21-7db1d36c55ee">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>And, for a long time, I hardly remember it now, but several days.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5054" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5052_flexid_cb6a3aa4-6ad4-4c51-ae4f-0eedcd41bb42">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>And, finally, Aramkhutu wounded him; he hit him with a rock, and then the other one who was dying threw one back with his final strength as he gathered strength, he threw it and hit Aramkhutu's arm, and wounded him slightly; he wounded him.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5603" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5601_flexid_86cf3cf6-3269-47eb-883a-1fb84d9f09f1">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>He [Ochokochi] died.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5647" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5645_flexid_ee493e77-2497-4871-9a49-ffafe931d5f2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Aramkhutu was a descendant of gods.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5731" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5729_flexid_8705ecad-e32a-4927-befc-78a3556899bd">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Later, he washed his arm in Tobavarchkhili.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5831" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5829_flexid_981bc5b1-e16f-4ba0-9e0f-f319205d07ad">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>That is why the water of Tobavarchkhili is holy, and, even presently, I held back from it, particularly, older generation; I too visit Tobavarchkhili. In recent years, I was there two or three times.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6264" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6262_flexid_9aeb59ab-66b0-43e0-bd57-fc0bdf1ab043">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>However, we, several men, visited it together, and, when we arrived, one of our group, a public officer jumped into it and bathed thereby.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6597" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6595_flexid_2da2fec5-fd23-4963-849e-37251cb54034">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>In an hour, please understand my words correctly, but in an hour, for five days before that there had been any rain anywhere, there was such a shower of rain that we ran downhill until reached a herdsman's tent.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7034" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7032_flexid_3a4d013f-b4a5-41ea-a8a7-b634ce169f81">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>And, as for Kuakantsalia.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7078" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7076_flexid_9f435911-d0ed-4d42-bc58-b4262eeca482">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Kuakantsalia is the rock that hit and wounded Aramkhutu. That one is Kuakantsalia.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7335" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7333_flexid_a7519574-6a28-4ab4-b5ce-9a09875a4ce2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Have you heard about Kuakantsalia?</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7421" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7419_flexid_05184c9f-9b80-4353-b575-1d195c45b220">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>Kuakantsalia really weighs twelve tons lying over the mountain. There is another rock over it, and, when you touch it with your finger, it begins knocking: mik-mik, kak-kak.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7790" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7788_flexid_cb20d226-44f1-42b2-8bd8-624644d6d0e7">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>The rock weighs twelve tons, ten or twelve tons, eh.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
    </TIER>
    <TIER LANG_REF="ka-Brai" LINGUISTIC_TYPE_REF="phrase-item"
        PARENT_REF="A_phrase-txt-xmf" TIER_ID="A_phrase-gls-ka-Brai">
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann8" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4_flexid_e102df48-df25-4510-ad17-f62fe11e4dd6">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ჯვარის ამ ტერიტორიას და ტობავარჩხილს რომ ეხება ამგვარი, ასეთნაირი  ლეგენდაა ერთი, რომელიც მე დამავალეს [ჩამეწერა], როცა ვიყავი სკოლაში, მერვე კლასში.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann395" ANNOTATION_REF="ann391_flexid_ad62b07b-6359-430c-a857-c20eebd1ff63">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ჩემმა მეზობელმა კაცმა,  მაგარმა, ვეფხისტყაოსანი ზეპირად რომ იცოდა და თავადაც ლექსებს წერდა, ასეთმა კაცმა, გალი სამუშია იყო და იმან ჩამაწერინა და ასეთი იყო ეს ლეგენდა.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann828" ANNOTATION_REF="ann824_flexid_6a1423e8-e9e6-428d-8895-3815fa59bcc8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ჯვარში დადიოდაო ყარაჩიდან, ოჩოკოჩი. ყარაჩი - ჩრდილოეთ კავკასია არის, ყარაჩაი-ჩერქეზეთის რესპუბლიკა რომელიცაა ახლა. რაღაც დევგმირი კაცი, რომელიც აქ მოვიდოდაო, დაავლებდა ხელს გოგოს, რომელიც მოეწონებოდაო და წაიყვანდაო.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1371" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1367_flexid_7c94aca2-c13c-4d70-8470-899d00ffbfa0">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ამას ვერაფრით ვუშველეთო ჯვარელებმა, ვერაფერი, ვერაფრით მოვერიეთო და დიდხანს წვალობდნენო ასე.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1686" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1682_flexid_5053dfbd-a485-4b5e-985e-292c65b0429b">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>და ასეთ დროს გამოჩნდა ასეთივე დევგმირი ვიღაცა, კეთილი კაცი და არამხუტუ რომ ერქვა, ასეთი კაცი [გამოჩნდა], არამხუტუ რომ ჰქვია.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1995" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1991_flexid_15b84b4f-0bd4-4227-a244-bfd94ddd88d2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>არც ის ყოფილა ადგილობრივი, მაგრამ გამოჩნდაო ეს.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2142" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2138_flexid_668e31d3-fe0b-4555-a61a-f55ce3c3716a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ჯვარელებმა ამას სთხოვეს დაგვეხმარეთო.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2283" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2279_flexid_afc20f71-3c17-4b97-80a2-78417401ab08">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ასეთი, ასეთი, ასე-ასეო [რომ მოუყვნენ], კარგიო -უთხრა და აქ დახვდაო წელს იმ კაცს, როცა მოვიდაო.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2528" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2524_flexid_f42dc4cd-e3db-4994-8cb5-1eb2ae553363">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ის დადიოდაო აგერ, ოხაჩქუე რომ ჰქვია მთას და იქ ჰქვია ყვირა [მთას და იქ].</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2688" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2684_flexid_0b49db13-b29e-420d-b1d0-c3fe6b69ae3f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>თავდაღმართში ხომ მოდის აგერ,  აქ მდინარე მაგანა მოდიოდა და აქეთ არის ყვირა, ორიათას მეტრამდეა მისი სიმაღლე; იქით ოხაჩქუეა, ესენი ორივე ძმებივით [აღმართულა] და ლამაზია, მაღლიდან რომ დახედავ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3081" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3077_flexid_43092591-3ab0-45c6-b0f9-fcf950668275">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ხოდა, იმ მთებში არის ჭები, სამკუთხედად ჩაწეული ადგილები.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3266" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3262_flexid_59207f39-3271-492a-8e45-0bb9e6b80883">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ზოგ ადგილას თოვლიც რჩება, "ჯიშტი" და მწყემსები იქ იმას დებენ, ხორცს ინახავენ და რაღაცეებს.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3530" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3526_flexid_68df40d4-2a35-4685-b066-7a4da8b77db8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ეს ბევრია იმ მთაზეც და ამ მთაზეც.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3670" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3666_flexid_30fedf67-a5f0-4e89-b138-59471355d987">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ამ ყვირას მთაზე არის ქუაცანცალია, ამას ამ ლეგენდის დასასრულისკენ [გეტყვით], ამასთან არის დაკავშირებული.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3920" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3916_flexid_d8e3c5f6-5b27-445e-803c-e9af707a520f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>მოვიდა. პირდაპირ რომ მოიხედა ახლა აქეთკენ, მთაში რომ იყო, აქედან დაუძახაო არამხუტუმ, არ ჩამოხვიდეო, აქ მე ვარო და არ ქნაო ეს.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4284" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4280_flexid_4d210514-d74e-45da-8a14-f1761ad0467a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>და ამან უთხრაო, ვინ ხარო შენ, ასე-ისეო და მოკლედ, მაშინ ვიჩხუბოთო.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4475" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4471_flexid_4a91d3b6-a8cd-41f2-8842-b19747618bfe">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ყვირაზე შედგა არამხუტუ, ყვირას მთაზე, ოხაჩქუეზე - ოჩოკოჩი და დაიწყეს ერთმანეთისთვის ქვების სროლა,</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4704" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4700_flexid_f27e6c83-2ac3-4dcb-9bd8-8f2a56b5dd7a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ახლა ესენი რომ ისროდნენ ეს ქვები რამხელები იქნებოდა, ხომ კი?!</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4904" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4900_flexid_df52ef5f-e0c1-4629-ba21-7db1d36c55ee">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ხოდა, კაი ხანი, რაღაც არ მახსოვს ახლა, მაგრამ რამდენიმე დღე.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5056" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5052_flexid_cb6a3aa4-6ad4-4c51-ae4f-0eedcd41bb42">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>და ბოლოს არამხუტუმ დაჭრაო, მოახვედრაო ის ქვა და მერე [იმან] მომაკვდავმა, აქეთ ესროლაო ბოლო ძალით, რადგან მოიკრიბაო, ესროლაო და არამხუტუს მოხვდაო ხელზე, მკლავზე და ოდნავ დაჭრაო რა, დაჭრა.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5605" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5601_flexid_86cf3cf6-3269-47eb-883a-1fb84d9f09f1">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ის [=ოჩოკოჩი] მოკვდა.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5649" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5645_flexid_ee493e77-2497-4871-9a49-ffafe931d5f2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>არამხუტუ ღმერთების შთამომავალი იყოო.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5733" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5729_flexid_8705ecad-e32a-4927-befc-78a3556899bd">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>მერე ტობავარჩხილში დაიბანაო ეს [=ასეთი] ხელი</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5833" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5829_flexid_981bc5b1-e16f-4ba0-9e0f-f319205d07ad">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ამის გამო ტობავარჩხილის წყალი არისო წმინდა და დღესაც მაინც ვერიდებოდი იმ ამბავს, მით უმეტეს - ძველები [=ძველი თაობა]; მეც დავდივარ ტობავარჩხილზე, ბოლო წლებში ორ-სამჯერ ვიყავი.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6266" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6262_flexid_9aeb59ab-66b0-43e0-bd57-fc0bdf1ab043">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>თუმცა ჩვენ ერთად ვიყავით [=რამდენიმე ვიყავით] და რომ წავედით, ერთი ჩვენი ჯგუფის წევრი, თანამდებობის კაცი, პირდაპირ ჩახტა და ტანი დაიბანა იქ მაინცდამაინც.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6599" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6595_flexid_2da2fec5-fd23-4963-849e-37251cb54034">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ერთი საათის განმავლობაში, სხვანაირად არ გამიგოთ, მაგრამ ერთ საათში, აქამდე ხუთი დღე რომ არ იყო არსად წვიმა, ისეთი თქეში მოვიდა, გავრბოდით თავდაღმართში, სანამ მწყემსის კარავამდე ჩავედით.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7036" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7032_flexid_3a4d013f-b4a5-41ea-a8a7-b634ce169f81">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ხოდა, რაც შეეხება ქუაცანცალიას.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7080" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7076_flexid_9f435911-d0ed-4d42-bc58-b4262eeca482">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ქუაქანცალია არისო, არამხუტუს აქეთ რომ მოხვდაო ბოლო ქვა და დაჭრაო, ის არისო ქუაქანცალია.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7337" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7333_flexid_a7519574-6a28-4ab4-b5ce-9a09875a4ce2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>თქვენ გაგებული გაქვთ ქუაქანცალია?</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7423" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7419_flexid_05184c9f-9b80-4353-b575-1d195c45b220">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ქუაქანცალია არის ნამდვილად თორმეტი ტონის ქვა, რომელიც დევს ამ მთაზე, ადევს მეორე ქვა და თითს რომ მიადებ ასეთნაირად, ისიც იწყებს კაკუნს: მიკ-მიკ, კაკ-კაკ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7792" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7788_flexid_cb20d226-44f1-42b2-8bd8-624644d6d0e7">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>თორმეტტონიანი ქვა არის, ათი-თორმეტი ტონიანი, აჰა.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
    </TIER>
    <TIER LANG_REF="xmf-fonipa" LINGUISTIC_TYPE_REF="phrase-item"
        PARENT_REF="A_phrase-txt-xmf" TIER_ID="A_phrase-gls-xmf-fonipa">
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4_flexid_e102df48-df25-4510-ad17-f62fe11e4dd6">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>d͡ʒvɑriʃi, ɑtɛ tʼɛritʼɔriɑsə ɔxuu dɔ tʼɔbɑvɑrt͡ʃxilət͡sən pɛri, lɛɡɛndɑ rɛ ɑrt ɑtɛʃnɛri, nɑmut mɑ mɑbruɔ kʼlɑsis vɔrdin tit͡sʼkʼəmɑ, kədmɑvɑlɛs skʼɔlɑs.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann394" ANNOTATION_REF="ann391_flexid_ad62b07b-6359-430c-a857-c20eebd1ff63">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ t͡ʃkimi mɛzɔbɛl kʼɔt͡ʃk dɔ mɑnɡɑr, vɛpxistʼqʼɑɔsɑnt͡s zɛpʼirɔ rɑɡɑdɑnd dɔ mu xɔlɔ lɛksɛps t͡ʃʼɑrəndən pɛr kʼɔt͡ʃk, ɡɑl sɑmuʃiɑ rdə dɔ tik kənmɔt͡ʃʼɑrɑpu dɔ ɑtɛʃnɛr rɛ tɛ lɛɡɛndɑɑ</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann827" ANNOTATION_REF="ann824_flexid_6a1423e8-e9e6-428d-8895-3815fa59bcc8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>d͡ʒvɑrʃɑvɑ miʃuɑ iʃ qʼɑrɑt͡ʃiʃə, qʼɑrɑt͡ʃ t͡ʃrdilɔɛt kʼɑvkʼɑsiɑ rɛ, qʼɑrɑt͡ʃɑi-t͡ʃɛrkɛzɛtis rɛspʼublikʼɑ rɛ ɑsɛn, qʼɑrɑt͡ʃʃɛvɑ ɡilɛʃuɑ ɔt͡ʃɔkʼɔt͡ʃi, dɛɛm kʼɔt͡ʃi mudɡɑrɛn, nɑmutiɑ ɑtɑkiɑ kimiʃuɑ dɔ  ɡɛuvɑluɑnduɑ tɛ mɛt͡sʼɔnɛbuduni pɛr d͡zɣɑbis dɔ midɛʔunɑnduɑ iʃɔ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1370" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1367_flexid_7c94aca2-c13c-4d70-8470-899d00ffbfa0">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>tɛʃɑ mutunk vɛmmɑxvɑrənɛsiɑ d͡ʒvɑrɛlɛpt͡s, mutunt͡su mutunit vɑmɑriɛbɛsiɑ tɛʃɑ dɔ brɛl xɑnt͡s it͡sʼvɑlɛbdɛsiɑ tɑʃi.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1685" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1682_flexid_5053dfbd-a485-4b5e-985e-292c65b0429b">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ ɑm drɔs ɡɑmkʼɔrt͡ʃkinduɑ  tɛ drɔs tɑki xɔlɔ ɑtɛd͡ʒɡurɑ dɛvɡmir midɡɑrɛni kʼɛtil kʼɔt͡ʃk dɔ ɑrɑmxutʼu d͡ʒɔxɔn pɛr kʼɔt͡ʃi, ɑrɑmxutʼu d͡ʒɔxɔn.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann1994" ANNOTATION_REF="ann1991_flexid_15b84b4f-0bd4-4227-a244-bfd94ddd88d2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ tinɑ xɔlɔ ɑdɡilɔbriv vɑʔɔpɛ, mɑrɑ ɡɑmkʼɔrt͡ʃkinduɑ tɛk.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2141" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2138_flexid_668e31d3-fe0b-4555-a61a-f55ce3c3716a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>d͡ʒvɑrɑlɛmk kɔtxiisiɑ tɛsə, kəmmɑxvɑritiɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2282" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2279_flexid_afc20f71-3c17-4b97-80a2-78417401ab08">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ɑtɛd͡ʒɡuɑ, ɑtɛd͡ʒɡuɑ tɑʃiɑ, tɑʃiɑn, ut͡sʼuɑ  - d͡ʒɡiriɑ ɔdɔ  kədɔxvɑduɑ t͡sʼi ti kʼɔt͡ʃk kəmɔrtuɑn.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2527" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2524_flexid_f42dc4cd-e3db-4994-8cb5-1eb2ae553363">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>tinɑ ɡilɛʃuɑ ɑtɑk ɔxɑt͡ʃkuɛ d͡ʒɔxɔ ɡvɑlɑ dɔ ɛtɛk d͡ʒɔxɔ qʼvirɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann2687" ANNOTATION_REF="ann2684_flexid_0b49db13-b29e-420d-b1d0-c3fe6b69ae3f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ɡimɛ xɔ mɔurt͡s ɑmɑri, ɑtɑk mɑɡɑnɑ mɔurdu mdinɑrɛ dɔ ɑtɑvrɛʃɛ rɛ  qʼviirɑ, ɔri ɑtɑs mɛtʼrɑmdɛɑ simɑɣlɛ, ɛurɛ ɔxɑt͡ʃkuɛ rɛ, tɛnɛp ʒirxɔlɔ ʒiʃɛ ɡinɑd͡ʒinɛkəni, skʼvɑm rɛnɑ d͡ʒimɑlɛpt͡sɑjɛ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3080" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3077_flexid_43092591-3ab0-45c6-b0f9-fcf950668275">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>xɔdɑ tɛk ɡvɑlɛpt͡s rɛ int͡ʃʼɛpi, ɑsɛ xɔlɔ, tis sɑmkʼutxɛdə ɑtɛʃnɛri inɔsɔpili ɑdɡilɛpə.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3265" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3262_flexid_59207f39-3271-492a-8e45-0bb9e6b80883">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>min dixɑs tir xɔlɔ inɔskʼid d͡ʒiʃtʼi dɔ t͡ʃʼqʼəʃɛp tɛk mudɑs inɔdvɑnɑ, xɔrt͡sis ʃɛnɑxənɑ ɑ  mudɡɑrɛnɛp pɛr.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3529" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3526_flexid_68df40d4-2a35-4685-b066-7a4da8b77db8">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>tinɑ brɛl rɛ ti ɡvɑlɑsət dɔ tɛ ɡvɑlɑsət.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3669" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3666_flexid_30fedf67-a5f0-4e89-b138-59471355d987">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ʔɑtɛ qʼvirɑsə rɛ kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑ, ɛs t͡sɑlkʼɛ dɑsr... tɛ lɛɡɛndɑʃ bɔlɔs rɛ ti kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑʃ  ɡurʃɛnə, dɑkʼɑvʃirɛbul rɛ tɛt͡sʼkʼəmɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann3919" ANNOTATION_REF="ann3916_flexid_d8e3c5f6-5b27-445e-803c-e9af707a520f">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>kəmɔrt, pʼirdɑpʼir kinkʼid͡ʒin ɑsɛ tɛurʃɛni ɡvɑlɑsdəni, tɑurʃɛ kədud͡zɑxuɑ ɑrɑmxutʼuk,  vɛɡmɑrtɑvɑ, tɑk mɑ vɔrɛkiɑ dɔ vɑkiminɑvɑ tɛnɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4283" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4280_flexid_4d210514-d74e-45da-8a14-f1761ad0467a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ  ɛk  ut͡sʼuɑ, si mi rɛk, tɑʃ tɛʃiɑ dɔ mɔkʼlɛt it͡sʼkʼəmɑ kibt͡ʃxubɑtiɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4474" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4471_flexid_4a91d3b6-a8cd-41f2-8842-b19747618bfe">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>qʼvirɑs kəɡmɔdərt ɑrɑmxutʼuk, qʼvirɑʃ ɡvɑlɑsə, ɔxɑt͡ʃkuɛs - ɔt͡ʃɔkʼɔt͡ʃik dɔ kudut͡ʃʼqʼɛs ɑrtiɑns kuɑlɛpiʃ ʔɔtɑmɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4703" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4700_flexid_f27e6c83-2ac3-4dcb-9bd8-8f2a56b5dd7a">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ɑsɛ ɛnɛp ɔʔɔtɑndɛs tɛ kuɑlɛp, muʃ mɑdidɑ iʔɛd, xɔm kɔ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann4903" ANNOTATION_REF="ann4900_flexid_df52ef5f-e0c1-4629-ba21-7db1d36c55ee">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>xɔdɑ, ibrd͡zɔlɛs kʼɑi xɑni, rɑɣɑt͡s vɑpʃ ɑsɛ, mɑrɑ tɛki  rɑmdɛnimɛ, muzmɑrɛn dɣɑsə.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5055" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5052_flexid_cb6a3aa4-6ad4-4c51-ae4f-0eedcd41bb42">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ bɔlɔs ɑrɑmxutʼukiɑ dɔt͡ʃʼkʼiruɑ, kəmɑxvɑmiluɑ ti kuɑ dɔ ukʼul mɑɣurudun  pɛrk ɑʃɔ kɑʔɔtuɑ ti bɔlɔ d͡zɑlɑt dɔʃɑqʼɑruuɑ rɑxɑntə, kɑʔɔtuɑ dɔ ɑrɑmxutʼus kəmɔxvɑduɑ xɛsə, kʼəlɛs dɔ t͡ʃʼi ɡɔt͡ʃʼkʼiruɑ rɑ, dɑt͡ʃʼrɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5604" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5601_flexid_86cf3cf6-3269-47eb-883a-1fb84d9f09f1">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ik dɔɣurə.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5648" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5645_flexid_ee493e77-2497-4871-9a49-ffafe931d5f2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɔ ɑrɑmxutʼu ɣɔrɔntɛpiʃ t͡ʃɑmɔmɑvɑliduɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5732" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5729_flexid_8705ecad-e32a-4927-befc-78a3556899bd">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ukʼuliɑ tʼɔbɑvɑrt͡ʃxils kinibɔnuɑ tɛ xɛ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann5832" ANNOTATION_REF="ann5829_flexid_981bc5b1-e16f-4ba0-9e0f-f319205d07ad">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>ɔdɔ ɑtiʃ ɡurʃɛn tʼɔbɑvɑrt͡ʃxiliʃ t͡sʼqʼɑr rɛniɑ t͡sʼmindɑ dɔ ɑmdɣɑ xɔlɔ ɑsɛ, mɑ xɔlɔ ɡiluurku tʼɔbɑvɑrt͡ʃxilʃɑ, ɑsɛ bɔlɔ t͡sʼɑnɛms ʒir sumʃɑx kuvɔrdi dɔ iʃɛn vɔridəd ti ɑmbɛs, mit umɛtʼɛs - d͡ʒvɛʃɛpi.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6265" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6262_flexid_9aeb59ab-66b0-43e0-bd57-fc0bdf1ab043">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>tumt͡sɑ t͡ʃki ɑrtɔ vɔrdit dɔ midɑprtitəni, ɑrt t͡ʃkən d͡ʒɡupiʃ t͡sʼɛvrik, tɑnmdɛbɔbɑʃ kʼɔt͡ʃk pʼirdɑpʼir kinɑsxɑpʼ dɔ tʼɑn ɡibɔn tɛk iʃɛniʃɛnə.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann6598" ANNOTATION_REF="ann6595_flexid_2da2fec5-fd23-4963-849e-37251cb54034">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>dɑ ɑrt sɑtiʃ dinɑxɑlɛ, ɑsɛ ʃxvɑnɛrɔ vɑɡɔmɡɑt, mɑrɑ ɑrt sɑtiʃ dinɑxɑlɛ, ɛsɛɡi xut dɣɑs vɑrd sɔtin t͡ʃʼvimɑ dɔ tid͡ʒɡuɑ mɛrɛxik ɡimɑlə, mibrulɛdit ɡimɛ, ɔndɔ ɛlɑptit t͡ʃʼqʼəʃiʃ kʼɑrɛʃɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7035" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7032_flexid_3a4d013f-b4a5-41ea-a8a7-b634ce169f81">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>xɔdɑ rɑt͡s ʃɛɛxɛbɑ kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑs.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7079" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7076_flexid_9f435911-d0ed-4d42-bc58-b4262eeca482">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑ rɛniɑ ɑrɑmxutʼus vɑrduɑɔ ɑʃɔ mɔxvɑd bɔlɔ kuɑkə dɔ t͡ʃʼkʼərən, tinɑ rɛniɑ kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7336" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7333_flexid_a7519574-6a28-4ab4-b5ce-9a09875a4ce2">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑ ɡənɑɡɛb kəɡɑpənɑnɔ tkvɑ?</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7422" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7419_flexid_05184c9f-9b80-4353-b575-1d195c45b220">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>kuɑkɑnt͡sɑliɑ nɑmdvil vtɔʒir tʼɔnɑʃ kuɑ,  nɑmut məkʼɔd͡z tɛ ɡvɑlɑsə, ɡɛd͡zə kʼənə mɑʒiɑ kuɑsə dɔ kʼətəs kənkʼɔdvɑnk ʔɑtɑʃ tinɑ xɔlɔ dɑ, dikʼɑkʼuɑns, mikʼ mikʼ, kʼɑkʼ kʼɑkʼ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
        <ANNOTATION>
            <REF_ANNOTATION ANNOTATION_ID="ann7791" ANNOTATION_REF="ann7788_flexid_cb20d226-44f1-42b2-8bd8-624644d6d0e7">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>vitɔʒir tʼɔniɑn kuɑ rɛ, vit vitɔʒir tʼɔniɑn kuɑ, ɑʔ.</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
            </REF_ANNOTATION>
        </ANNOTATION>
    </TIER>
